data.title: node2 exception widget format
data.body:
For running the node2 adapter in VS, I need to set all relevant fields in the ExceptionInfo response: https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode-debugadapter-node/blob/master/protocol/src/debugProtocol.ts#L1017

The only ones we display in VS Code are 'details.stackTrace' and 'description'. I can set 'description' to the Error's message, and 'stackTrace' to its stackTrace, but an Error stackTrace typically contains the message, so it would show up twice, so I currently don't set the description.

I could get around this by extracting the message from the stackTrace, and setting both properties, but VS Code displays the two props with a space between them in the exception widget.

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/323878/30354327-d07d481c-97e0-11e7-991d-7a2f8ad17280.png)

Which is fine for other debuggers but looks wrong for JS where I expect the stack trace to look a certain way.

Do you have any ideas how to meet all the constraints, without adding an option to the debug adapter or a check for 'vs'? Or maybe that's just what I need to do.

@isidorn @weinand
